      <byline class="print_byline">AP</byline>
      <dateline>SAVANNAH, Ga., April 23</dateline>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>A man who was chosen foreman of a Federal grand jury in January has been jailed and fined for missing the jury's monthly three-day sessions in February, March and April.</p>
        <p>The foreman, Edwin Paul Schaffhauser, who insists that he called in sick on those days, spent the weekend in jail, his second weekend behind bars as he works off a five-day sentence imposed by Federal District Judge B. Avant Edenfield for contempt of court.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>A man who was chosen foreman of a Federal grand jury in January has been jailed and fined for missing the jury's monthly three-day sessions in February, March and April.</p>
        <p>The foreman, Edwin Paul Schaffhauser, who insists that he called in sick on those days, spent the weekend in jail, his second weekend behind bars as he works off a five-day sentence imposed by Federal District Judge B. Avant Edenfield for contempt of court.</p>
        <p>Judge Edenfield also fined Mr. Schaffhauser $1,000 and removed him from the jury.</p>
      </block>
